    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <h3>Are nicotine pouches safe?</h3>
    <p>Nicotine pouches are less harmful than cigarettes because they don't involve burning or inhalation of smoke. However, nicotine itself is addictive and not risk-free. If you have cardiovascular concerns, are pregnant, or take medications that interact with nicotine, consult a healthcare provider. Nicotine-free alternatives like Zeronito or VELO Zero offer the habit without the stimulant.</p>

    <h3>How long does a nicotine pouch last?</h3>
    <p>Most standard pouches last 45–60 minutes. Mini pouches typically last 20–30 minutes due to their smaller size. Stronger pouches can feel "spent" slightly faster because the nicotine is absorbed more quickly.</p>

    <h3>Will nicotine pouches stain my teeth?</h3>
    <p>Unlike snus or tobacco products, nicotine pouches contain no tobacco and won't stain your teeth. They're white, and the pouches remain in your mouth without direct contact with your tooth surface.</p>

    <h3>Can I use nicotine pouches if I'm new to nicotine?</h3>
    <p>Yes, but start low. Begin with a 4–5 mg pouch and use for 20–30 minutes. If you want to avoid nicotine entirely, our nicotine-free range (Zeronito, VELO Zero, X-booster) offers the same ritual without the drug. <a href="/blog/nicotine-pouch-flavour-guide">Learn more about starting out</a>.</p>

    <h3>What's the difference between slim and mini pouches?</h3>
    <p>Slim pouches are the standard smaller format — discreet and comfortable. Mini pouches are even smaller and nearly invisible, lasting 20–30 minutes. If maximum discretion is your priority, mini is best; if you prefer longer sessions, slim is the better choice.</p>

